==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Greaser
<hw>Greas"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, greases; specifically, a person employed to lubricate the
working parts of machinery, engines, carriages, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A nickname sometimes applied in contempt to a
Mexican or other Latin-American of the lowest type; -- derogatory and
offensive.</def> <mark>[Low, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>grease-gun</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>grease gun</ent>⟦br⟧
